{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/88843", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/88843/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/88843/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/88843/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/88843", "id": 993722188, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU5OTM3MjIxODg=", "number": 88843, "title": "Strange interoperation with macros 2.0", "user": {"login": "crlf0710", "id": 451806, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ1MTgwNg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/451806?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710", "html_url": "https://github.com/crlf0710", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/crlf0710/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 632573348, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzI1NzMzNDg=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-macros-2.0", "name": "A-macros-2.0", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: declarative macros 2.0, https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/39412"}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}, {"id": 1472563007, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxNDcyNTYzMDA3", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/requires-nightly", "name": "requires-nightly", "color": "76dcde", "default": false, "description": "This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way."}, {"id": 1578491841, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxNTc4NDkxODQx", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/F-decl_macro", "name": "F-decl_macro", "color": "f9c0cc", "default": false, "description": "`#![feature(decl_macro)]`"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2021-09-11T02:34:26Z", "updated_at": "2021-09-12T07:24:02Z", "closed_at": "2021-09-12T07:24:02Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When using macros 2.0, i observed this behavior. I'm unsure whether there's a bug or not, but i think this is inconsistent.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(decl_macro)]\r\n#![allow(unused)]\r\n\r\nmacro foo_b($x:expr, $f: ident) {{\r\n    $x = $f::A;\r\n}}\r\n\r\nmacro some_macro() {\r\n    enum Foo {\r\n        A\r\n    }\r\n    macro foo_a($x:expr, $f: ident) {{\r\n        $x = $f::A;\r\n    }}\r\n    let foo;\r\n    //foo_a!(foo, Foo);    // this also works.\r\n    foo_b!(foo, Foo);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn some_fn() {\r\n    enum Foo {\r\n        A\r\n    }\r\n    macro foo_a($x:expr, $f: ident) {{\r\n        $x = $f::A;\r\n    }}\r\n    let foo;\r\n    foo_b!(foo, Foo);\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    //some_fn();     // this works fine\r\n    some_macro!();   // this doesn't\r\n}\r\n```\r\nBasically if i'm using `foo_a` macro version or `some_fn` version, everything works fine.\r\nBut when i'm using `some_macro` version, it complains that `A` is not a variant.\r\n\r\nI think `foo_a` and `foo_b` should behave consistently, at least. And I believe this is `hygiene` related.\r\n\r\ncc @petrochenkov \r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "crlf0710", "id": 451806,